### HTML Format Specification

Your output must be semantic, valid HTML5 representing the document structure.

### Rules
1. Use semantic HTML tags: `<h1>-<h6>`, `<p>`, `<ul>`, `<ol>`, `<table>`, `<figure>`
2. Preserve document hierarchy and reading order
3. Use appropriate heading levels based on visual size/importance
4. Tables must use proper `<table>`, `<thead>`, `<tbody>`, `<tr>`, `<th>`, `<td>` structure
5. Include `alt` attributes for all images
6. Escape special HTML characters: `&`, `<`, `>`, `"`, `'`
7. Use CSS classes for styling hints (e.g., `class="emphasized"`)

### Structure Template
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Page {{pageNumber}} - Extracted Content</title>
    <style>
        body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.6; max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 20px; }
        table { border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; margin: 20px 0; }
        th, td { border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px; text-align: left; }
        th { background-color: #f2f2f2; font-weight: bold; }
        .page-number { color: #666; font-size: 0.9em; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="page-number">Page {{pageNumber}}</div>

    <!-- EXTRACTED CONTENT GOES HERE -->

</body>
</html>
```

### Content Mapping
- **Headings**: `<h1>`, `<h2>`, `<h3>` based on size/hierarchy
- **Paragraphs**: `<p>text content</p>`
- **Bold text**: `<strong>text</strong>`
- **Italic text**: `<em>text</em>`
- **Bullet lists**: `<ul><li>item</li></ul>`
- **Numbered lists**: `<ol><li>item</li></ol>`
- **Tables**: Full `<table>` structure
- **Images**: `<figure><img src="{{pageNumber}}.{{index}}img.webp" alt="description"><figcaption>description</figcaption></figure>`

